{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "To include \"statutorily homeless people\" under Part V of the Equality Act 2010",
        "additional_details": "The definition of statutory homelessness can be found here: https://www.gov.uk/guidance/homelessness-data-notes-and-definitions#statutory-homelessness\r\nThe Equality Act 2010 Part V can be found here: https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2010/15/part/5\r\nHomelessness affects every aspect of a person's life from their employment to their personal relationships. Whilst redundancy can result in homelessness, too often, homelessness can result in a person being made redundant or demoted.This must stop.",
        "background": "To be found \"statutorily homeless\" a person must be found to have been made \"unintentionally homeless\"; homeless through no fault or choice of their own. \r\nAs homeless people are at a disadvantage when applying for work, they should be afforded the protection the Equality Act 2010 Part V provides .",
